<subSubSection id="6EDC654FFE44FF8FFF0AFB5A585DFA38" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="267936C4FE44FF8FFF0AFB5A585DFA38" blockId="4.[166,1225,1108,1423]" pageId="4" pageNumber="25">
Biology. 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE44FF8FFE8CFB5A5E75FB18" author="Neff, S. E. &amp; Berg, C. O." box="[349,563,1172,1199]" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 113" refId="ref6735" refString="Neff, S. E., Berg, C. O. 1966. Biology and immature stages of malacophagous Diptera of the genus Sepedon (Sciomyzidae). Virginia Agricultural Experimental Station Bulletin, 566, 1 - 113." type="journal article" year="1966">Neff, Berg (1966)</bibRefCitation>
described the complete life cycle and figured all the immature stages. That was one of the first sciomyzids known as predators of aquatic snails (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE44FF8FFF2AFB1A5D8CFB58" author="Neff, S. E. &amp; Berg, C. O." box="[251,458,1236,1263]" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 113" refId="ref6735" refString="Neff, S. E., Berg, C. O. 1966. Biology and immature stages of malacophagous Diptera of the genus Sepedon (Sciomyzidae). Virginia Agricultural Experimental Station Bulletin, 566, 1 - 113." type="journal article" year="1966">Neff, Berg, 1966</bibRefCitation>
). Many snails species belonging to 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE44FF8FFC54FB1A5851FB59" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1815" box="[901,1047,1236,1262]" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Lymnaeidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE44FF8FFBF6FB1A58D6FB59" authorityName="Fitzinger" authorityYear="1833" box="[1063,1168,1236,1262]" class="Gastropoda" family="Physidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Physidae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE44FF8FFF77FB3A5D72FAB9" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1815" box="[166,308,1268,1294]" class="Gastropoda" family="Planorbidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Planorbidae</taxonomicName>
particularly some 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE44FF8FFDDAFB3A5EA6FAB8" box="[523,736,1268,1295]" class="Gastropoda" family="Planorbidae" genus="Biomphalaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE44FF8FFDDAFB3A5EEDFAB9" box="[523,683,1268,1294]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="25">Biomphalaria</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
implicated as intermediate host of human schistosomiasis (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE44FF8FFEBCFADA5E7EFA98" author="Neff, S. E. &amp; Berg, C. O." box="[365,568,1300,1327]" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 113" refId="ref6735" refString="Neff, S. E., Berg, C. O. 1966. Biology and immature stages of malacophagous Diptera of the genus Sepedon (Sciomyzidae). Virginia Agricultural Experimental Station Bulletin, 566, 1 - 113." type="journal article" year="1966">Neff, Berg, 1966</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE44FF8FFDA2FADB5EE1FA98" box="[627,679,1301,1327]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="25">Iran</collectingCountry>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE44FF8FFD67FADA5F18FA98" author="Tirgari, S." box="[694,862,1300,1327]" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" pagination="103 - 104" refId="ref7073" refString="Tirgari, S. 1977. Theoretical and experimental evidences of biological control of aquatic snails by snail-killing flies in relation to schistosomiasis (Diptera: Sciomyzidae) (Sepedon sphegea). Summary. First Mediterranean Conference of Parasitology, Oct. 5 - 10, 1977, Izmir, Turkey, 103 - 104." type="proceedings paper" year="1977">Tirgari (1977)</bibRefCitation>
used their larvae for his field experiments against Planrbidae. Also, 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE44FF8FFDB8FAFB5FCFFAF8" author="Mc Donnell, R. J. &amp; Mulkeen, C. J. &amp; Gormally, M. J." box="[617,905,1332,1359]" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" pagination="291 - 301" refId="ref6609" refString="Mc Donnell, R. J., Mulkeen, C. J., Gormally, M. J. 2005. Sexual dimorphism and the impact of temperature on the pupal and adult stages Sepedon spinipes spinipes, a potential biological control agent of fascioliasis. Entomologia Experimentalis et Applicata, 115, 291 - 301." type="journal article" year="2005">Mc Donnell et al. (2005)</bibRefCitation>
collected third-instar larva feeding on 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE44FF8FFEF6FA9A5F7CFAD8" authority="(Annandale, Prashad, 1919)" baseAuthorityName="Annandale, Prashad" baseAuthorityYear="1919" box="[295,826,1364,1391]" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Radix" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="gedrosiana">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE44FF8FFEF6FA9A5DA9FAD9" box="[295,495,1364,1390]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="25">Radix gedrosiana</emphasis>
(Annandale, Prashad, 1919)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE44FF8FFCAEFA9B5FF7FAD8" box="[895,945,1365,1391]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="25">Iran</collectingCountry>
(Shushtar). This species is multivoltine, and overwinters as adult (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE44FF8FFD5AFABA5F0BFA39" author="Neff, S. E. &amp; Berg, C. O." box="[651,845,1396,1423]" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 113" refId="ref6735" refString="Neff, S. E., Berg, C. O. 1966. Biology and immature stages of malacophagous Diptera of the genus Sepedon (Sciomyzidae). Virginia Agricultural Experimental Station Bulletin, 566, 1 - 113." type="journal article" year="1966">Neff, Berg, 1966</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE44FF8FFC89FABB5856FA38" author="Gaponov, S. P." box="[856,1040,1396,1423]" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" pagination="54 - 63" refId="ref6197" refString="Gaponov, S. P. 2016. Fauna and bioecology of snail-killing flies (Diptera: Sciomyzidae) in the central black soil region of Russia. Proceedings of Voronezh State University. Ser.: Chemistry. Biology. Pharmacy, 1, 54 - 63." type="journal article" year="2016">Gaponov, 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
